modules.description: Provides functions to read and write raw Ethernet frames, including parsing and constructing headers for Ethernet, IP, and UDP protocols. Operates on byte buffers and structured data types representing network packets. Enables low-level network communication in custom or embedded network stacks.

Provides functions to manage network interfaces, including disconnecting, writing packets, and listening for incoming traffic. Operates on types like Cstruct.t for packet data, Macaddr.t for MAC addresses, and error for error handling. Used to interact with tap devices, send and receive network packets, and monitor interface statistics.
